tballs (approx. Ø 4 cm) then place on a plate and set aside in fridge for 1 hour. Clean mixing bowl and after 40 minutes prepare sauce."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Sauce"},{"content":"Place oil, onions and garlic in mixing bowl then chop <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then cook <b>10 min\/98°C\/speed <b>."},{"content":"Add tomatoes, oregano, sugar (if using), salt and pepper then, with simmering basket in place of measuring cup, simmer <b>15 min\/98°C\/speed 0.5<b>. Season to taste and add red wine vinegar (if using) then keep warm."},{"content":"Heat a little oil in a frying pan over a medium heat. Add meatballs in batches and fry until golden brown all over. Place in a serving dish and pour over tomato sauce. Sprinkle with chopped parsley and serve."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Delicious served with spaghetti, linguini or tagliatelle.","Use swordfish instead of tuna.","Sicilian cuisine is considered one of the healthiest in Italy with its emphasis on fresh seafood, like tuna and swordfish, and fresh vegetables and fruits like tomatoes, olives, citrus and artichokes. We’ve brought the vibrant flavours of Sicily to these unusual meatballs, which feature fresh tuna instead of the usual pork or beef. Typically tuna steaks are lightly seared on a barbecue or grill, however, they work really well prepared in this way and served with a deliciously rich tomato sauce."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h 45m","4 portions"]}